entries.femaleVariant: They've launched the drones!
Fuck. I just realized something.
I'm glad we're doing this.
So, what happened with the cop?
Are we all set?
Mhm.
So jack in, let's get the hell out of here.
[Jack in] You got it.
Can't say I know how it was supposed to be. But somehow I feel...
Meaning, leaving?
Mhm. Said goodbye to the girls at Lizzie's today. Almost all were sure I'd flake, back out.
But I had this inkling that everything was different up north. That some bright fucking future awaited me there.
This is your big, new beginning. So you have to start it like a real nomad, behind the proverbial wheel.
I will deal with the nitro. The mix will go straight to the cylinders.
If I don't synch it just right manually, it could blow us to bits.
River? Came to say goodbye.
Fuck. That is not how it was supposed to be, was it?
Even started a pool, you know, 'bout me limpin' back home, tail between my legs. Like many of 'em, more times than they'd care to admit.
I ever tell you I planned this with Evelyn? A flight out of Night City to bliss?
Think I know what comes next – once you wound up on the other side and nothin' changed, you thought Night City was the answer, everything'd change there.
entries.maleVariant: Yeah, think I know what comes next – once you wound up on the other side and nothin' changed, you thought Night City was the answer, everything would change there.

entries.femaleVariant: Yes... And you know the tale's end, too.
No. Might be the same place on the other side, same space. But you're different, totally different.
All in all, you're right. And I have you. And the rest of these clowns.
A new beginning.

entries.maleVariant: Know what? To see Kerry Eurodyne looking lost in the middle of nowhere... that was truly a sight.
Kerry came out to say goodbye. Said he still had unfinished biz in Night City.
Thinking about it now, doubt it could've gone any other way. But you know what?

entries.femaleVariant: Don't try to name it. Just enjoy it. I feel the same way.
Exactly what you wanted.

entries.maleVariant: That was not how it was supposed to go, was it?

entries.femaleVariant: What?
The border wall. It wasn't here when I was little, I never imagined it would be.
Don't slow down, Panam. Not yet.
Carol! Cassidy! Get moving!
I'm heading west and activating the jammers.
They've marked me, I'm turning east to get 'em off your tail. G'luck, kids!
Got a feeling majority's gonna be out some eddies.
entries.maleVariant: Got a feeling the majority's gonna be out some eddies.

entries.femaleVariant: Fuck. I just realized something.
What's wrong?
The border wall. When I was little, it wasn't there, obviously.
But I sensed everything was different in the north. That something great awaited me there. A bright fucking future.
Yeah, I think I know what comes next – once you made it here and nothing changed, you thought Night City was the answer, everything'd change there.
entries.maleVariant: Yeah, think I know what comes next – once you wound up on the other side and nothin' changed, you thought Night City was the answer, everything would change there.

entries.femaleVariant: Yes... And you know the tale's end, too. I'm returning. Right back to where I started.
No. Might be the same place on the other side, same space. But you're different, totally different.
All in all, you may be right.
I'm returning. Right back to where I started. Fuck.
Dreamed about what we'd do when we finally got the chance…
I'm sorry, Judy.
Don't let it bother you. I won't. Mentioned it 'cause feels like I should let that dream go, too.
Hm, say goodbye... For a while? For good?
We pretty much said that's that. Night City – he doesn't wanna leave. Can't, he says.
See you on the other side!
Let's ride!
You ready?
Been ready always.
Then hit it – home stretch, full speed ahead!
You got it.
Mostly go straight, go around the bigger holes and don't lose the rest, got it?
Think that's best avoided.
The nitro is ready.
Got nothin' left to say.
Say goodbye to Night City, it's your last chance.
Well?
It's perfect – all great, Panam. We're goin' home.
We're ready. After you, Panam.
Besides, you'll come to understand it once we're on the other side. You'll see.
Start 'er up, the wheel is yours.
What?
Like I just stepped out of a room I'd been locked inside of. Dunno what that feeling is. Hope? Fulfillment?

entries.maleVariant: Feel like I just stepped out of a room I'd been locked inside of. Dunno what that feeling is. Hope? Fulfillment?

entries.femaleVariant: V, they'll getcha if you stray too wide!
Stay close to the others! To bite it now would be plain stupid!
[Breathe free]
